title: Pet-Poisoning Cane Toads Cross Border Into NSW | 10 News+
description: Deadly cane toads have hopped the border from Queensland to New South Wales and are creeping closer to the city. The toads release a powerful poison that they use to defend themselves if attacked, placing household pets, like cats and dogs, at risk. Residents are being urged not to harm the animal and to report sightings to the NSW Department of Primary Industries or on 'ToadScan' (feralscan.org.au/toadscan) to help prevent this invasive pest from establishing locally. title: Final Day Of Summer Unleashes Wild Weather Across Australia | 10 News
description: The final day of summer has delivered wild weather across multiple states. Parts of South Australia are on flood watch after a heavy deluge, with some towns recording their wettest days on record — and more rain still on the way. Victoria is bracing for more storms as Autumn arrives tomorrow, while inland Queensland communities remain cut off by floodwaters, with no end in sight.
